<TEXT>
<P>
HOT FLASH: Talk about timely. Just as 2 Live Crew is being prosecuted for 
making allegedly obscene rap records, Rhino Records is putting together a 
collection of lascivious R&amp;B gems that would bring a blush to the cheeks of 
pop morality crusader Tipper Gore (who frequently boasts about her love for old 
rock 'n' roll). 
</P>
<P>
Compiled by Rhino A&amp;R exec James Austin, the compilation, titled "Risque 
Rhythm," is due in September and features a host of of double-entendre classics 
that can be seen as the progenitors of today's raunchy rap hits. The 18-song 
package includes Bull Moose Jackson's "Big Ten-Inch Record," Tampa Red's "Let 
Me Play With Your Poodle," the Dominoes' "Sixty Minute Man" and Wynonie Harris' 
"Keep on Churning (Till the Butter Comes)." 
