<TEXT>
<P>
GOING IN STYLE: Dead Boys' lead singer Stiv Bators, who was hit by a car and 
killed recently, was always a Doors fan. So much so, says I.R.S. Records 
(Bators' label), that Stiv, according to his wishes, was cremated and had his 
ashes spread on Jim Morrison's grave in Paris. . . . When Slaughter (who is 
currently on a nationwide tour with Kiss) hits Philadelphia for several dates 
beginning Tuesday, the band will skip the local hotel circuit -- and stay at 
the home of a die-hard fan, Dan Zimmerman, who invited the group to hang with 
him (at his parents' house, of course). 
</P>
<P>
When the group heard that the 19-year-old fan's house had a huge back yard, 
swimming pool and live-in gourmet cook, they said: 'Later, Holiday Inn!' 
Actually, the band members warned the family that they'd have a huge tour bus 
parked in front of the house, with five raucous roadies on board -- but the 
invitation stood. "It's gonna be great," said bassist Dana Strum. "The parents 
said they were looking forward to our visit." 
</P>
