<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE REAL POISON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I found Patrick Goldstein's piece "Farrell Is Addicted to Not Covering Up His 
Covers" (June 10) extremely disturbing. I cannot believe what is happening 
concerning censorship. 
</P>
<P>
I was outraged when I went into a record shop a few years ago in search of 
Poison's "Open Up and Say Ahh" and instead of finding the original album cover, 
I found a "more suitable" version. The album cover was altered because the 
original version was allegedly "too satanic." 
</P>
<P>
I sympathize with Percy Farrell of Jane's Addiction. I do not think he should 
compromise by changing his original album cover in order to please the 
narrow-minded "moral majority." 
</P>
<P>
Conservative legislators and others are trying to limit my choices as a 
consumer and are undermining the constitutional rights of many artists. 
</P>
<P>
ARIEL CARMONA JR. 
</P>
<P>
Hollywood 
</P>
</TEXT>
