<HEADLINE>
<P>
CORPORAL PUNISHMENT OUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HONG KONG 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hong Kong is to end the use of corporal punishment in its prisons, the 
government said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
A statement said a Correctional Services Department study had shown there were 
better ways to rehabilitate prisoners than beating them with a cane. 
</P>
</TEXT>
