</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
ILLINOIS DISASTER DECLARED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
President Bush declared Friday that a major disaster exists in Illinois as a 
result of severe storms, tornadoes and flooding last month. The President's 
action makes federal funding available to individuals and local governments in 
a seven-county area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
