<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: VENTURA; 
</P>
<P>
STUDENT CHOSEN FOR LEADERSHIP SEMINAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ADRIANNE GOODMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Ventura High School sophomore will be among six students representing the 
state at the International Leadership Seminar, a conference that attracts 
students from around the world. 
</P>
<P>
Sean Osborne, 16, was selected from among 225 students who competed at 
Pepperdine University in a leadership seminar sponsored by the nonprofit 
foundation earlier this month. 
</P>
<P>
Sean, who will represent central California, will be among more than 200 
students from 30 countries, including the Soviet Union and China, at the 
all-expense-paid conference in St. Paul, Minn. in July. 
</P>
<P>
Students were nominated to participate on the basis of recommendations from 
their high school principals, said program director Bob Shirilla. Finalists 
were selected based on their performance in essay writing and interviews before 
a panel of judges, he said. 
</P>
<P>
The conference is sponsored by the Hugh O'Brian Youth Leadership Foundation, a 
national, nonprofit organization founded in 1958 that aims to promote 
leadership skills and critical thinking among high school sophomores. ADRIANNE 
GOODMAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
