<HEADLINE>
<P>
INMATE DEATH ATTRIBUTED TO NATURAL CAUSES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 42-year-old man who was in sheriff's custody died Saturday in Tri-City 
Medical Center in Oceanside, apparently of natural causes, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The victim was identified as Raymond Albert Brinkerhoff, an Oceanside truck 
driver. 
</P>
<P>
Brinkerhoff had been in sheriff's custody since March 28 on drug and weapons 
charges, a sheriff's spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
On June 15, the spokeswoman said, authorities transported him from the county 
jail in Vista to Tri-City Hospital after he had vomited blood and complained of 
abdominal pains. He had a history of bleeding ulcers and a cancerous throat 
condition, according to the sheriff's office. 
</P>
<P>
Brinkerhoff suffered cardiac failure in the hospital early Saturday and was 
pronounced dead at 5:37 a.m., said a spokesman for the county Medical 
Examiner's office. 
</P>
</TEXT>
