<HEADLINE>
<P>
ENCINITAS GIRL, 4, DROWNS IN POOL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 4-year-old Encinitas girl died Saturday, an apparent drowning victim, after 
losing consciousness while playing in shallow water in a community pool, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The victim was identified as Elizabeth Mealy. 
</P>
<P>
The girl was playing in three feet of water in an Encinitas pool when she began 
to drown about 10:30 a.m., possibly after she hit her head on the bottom, said 
a spokesman for the San Diego County Medical Examiner's office. Her mother was 
nearby, the spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
Efforts to revive the girl were unsuccessful, and she succumbed about an hour 
later at Scripps Memorial Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
She was the 10th youth age 14 or under to die because of an apparent drowning 
in San Diego County thus far in 1990, said Mark Morelli, a spokesman for 
Children's Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
Morelli said the number of drownings and near-drownings among area children has 
increased but that he does not know the reason. 
</P>
</TEXT>
