<HEADLINE>
<P>
KRUSEMAN WINS THREE-QUARTER MIDGET MAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PAUL OLSON, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cory Kruseman, 19, of Ventura won the three-quarter Midget 20-lap USAC Western 
States Series main event at Ventura Raceway on Saturday night before 2,380. 
</P>
<P>
Jason Gibb of Long Beach held a narrow lead over Kruseman for 16 laps before 
spinning out in Turn 4. 
</P>
<P>
Kruseman took the lead, but was locked in a tight battle with Page Jones of 
Rolling Hills. 
</P>
<P>
Jones edged past Kruseman on Lap 18. But Jones, with Kruseman on his tail, hit 
a groove and slid sideways on Lap 19, giving Kruseman the space he needed to go 
on to win. 
</P>
<P>
Jeff Drake of Valencia finished second and Rob Hansen of Simi Valley third. 
Jones was fifth. Frank Pedregon of Gardena led wire-to-wire to win the Midget 
30-lap main event. Hank Butcher of San Leandro edged George Ito of Ventura to 
finish second. 
</P>
<P>
City of Industry's Robby Flock and Anaheim's Gary Howard each won a 10-lap 
Midget heat race. The eight-lap heat race winners for three-quarter Midgets 
were Jim Styer of Tujunga, Steve Kellick of Ventura, Ito, and Tom Morley of 
Woodland Hills. 
</P>
<P>
Frank Deiny Jr. of Burbank won the flip-plagued three-quarter Midget 10-lap 
semi-main event to lead a four-car contingent transferring to the main event 
from a 19-car starting field. 
</P>
<P>
Also making the transfer were Gibb, Gary Schroeder of Burbank, and Hansen. 
</P>
<P>
Fast one-lap qualifying times were set by Flock in the Midgets at 13.156 
seconds and Drake in the three-quarter Midgets at 14.144. 
</P>
</TEXT>
