<HEADLINE>
<P>
ON SAM HALL KAPLAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It must have been astonishing to all to read the unnoticeable caption on Sam 
Hall Kaplan's departure from the L.A. Times (June 3). 
</P>
<P>
With great irony the Real Estate's lead article about termites leaves me 
wondering whether the pests have already begun to take their toll on your 
paper. 
</P>
<P>
The leaders of this section have removed the backbone, which has so 
strengthened for so long what little spine existed in the Real Estate pages. 
</P>
<P>
Now you have a rather odd collection of slithering media-hyped articles 
appealing to a primordial readership at best. 
</P>
<P>
JACK HILLBRAND 
</P>
<P>
Santa Monica 
</P>
