<HEADLINE>
<P>
GARDENER'S CHECKLIST: GARDENING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For dedicated gardeners, here are suggestions from the California Assn. of 
Nurseryman on what to do in the garden this week: 
</P>
<P>
If feeding camellias and azaleas with an acid-promoting fertilizer doesn't 
"green" them up, use an iron chelate available at your local garden center. 
</P>
<P>
Soak hanging basket plants under a sprinkler or in a tub every now and then to 
insure roots are getting thoroughly irrigated. 
</P>
<P>
Bougainvillea bloom will be intensified if you keep the plants on the dry side. 
If they're not blooming at all, chances are you're watering too much. 
</P>
<P>
Chrysanthemums bought in bloom this month can be cut back when flowering is 
finished for a second bloom in the fall. 
</P>
</TEXT>
