<P>
LOOKING AT JEWELS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In Stephen Williams' story, "Sydney in '90 Is Rocking, Not Waltzing, Matilda," 
June 3, he failed to mention that the opals in the geological museum in the 
Rocks district are really lovely and free from government tax. They are more 
reasonably priced than elsewhere and consist of loose stones as well as cuff 
links, earrings, rings and pendants. 
</P>
<P>
SHARLENE G. ROTH 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
