<HEADLINE>
<P>
DC-10 RETURNS TO LAX; ENGINE BLAMED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A UTA French Airlines DC-10 bound for Tahiti was forced to return to Los 
Angeles International Airport early Saturday because of a malfunctioning 
engine, but landed safely, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Flight 503 landed at 5:07 a.m., more than an hour after the Federal Aviation 
Administration was notified that the plane was flying with one engine shut down 
and was returning to the airport, an FAA spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
The 189 passengers were put up in hotels for the night while the airplane was 
repaired and another flight scheduled for Sunday, an airport operations 
spokesman said. 
</P>
