<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: MOSLEY, 2 OTHER U.S. BOXERS BEAT SOVIETS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Victories by Shane Mosley of Pomona and two other U.S. boxers helped the North 
American team dominate U.S. Olympic Cup boxing competition Saturday at Salt 
Lake City. 
</P>
<P>
Eric Griffin and Raul Marquez, both of Houston, and Mosley all won decisions 
over Soviet fighters. 
</P>
<P>
Griffin beat Evgeni Novosleov in the 106-pound division, Mosley defeated Leonid 
Bronnikov in a 132-pound bout and Marquez outpointed Andrei Tracenko in a 
battle of 147-pounders. 
</P>
<P>
The North American squad, which also includes boxers from Cuba and Canada, won 
five of seven bouts against a European team. 
</P>
<P>
North America's other two victories were by Cubans -- Enrique Carrion at 126 
pounds and Felix Savon in the heavyweight match. 
</P>
<P>
The U.S. Olympic Cup, a two-day competition between athletes from North America 
and Europe, concludes today. Boxing is one of five sports. 
</P>
</TEXT>
