<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nolan Ryan has bought the Danbury State Bank in Danbury, Tex., 13 miles south 
of his hometown of Alvin. 
</P>
<P>
"It's the greatest thing that ever happened to this bank," bank president 
Annette Mandola said. "I can't imagine us working for him." 
</P>
<P>
Ryan, a pitcher for the Texas Rangers, purchased the bank, the only one in 
Danbury, a town of 1,500, from a group of investors in the El Campo and Louise 
area in Brazoria County. 
</P>
<P>
The purchase price was undisclosed. But the bank has $10.9 million in assets 
and $9.3 million in deposits. And Ryan is the sole owner. 
</P>
