<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY RIDERS IN SPEEDWAY QUALIFYING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The second round of qualifying for the world speedway motorcycle championship 
is scheduled today with four Americans competing in the Overseas Final at 
Coventry, England. 
</P>
<P>
Shawn Moran of Huntington Beach, winner of the American Final at Long Beach 
three weeks ago, leads a group of Americans that also includes Ronnie Correy of 
Fullerton, Rick Miller of Reseda and Billy Hamill of Monrovia. 
</P>
<P>
Correy was the only American rider to qualify for the world championship last 
year, finishing in a four-way tie for eighth place. The last American to win a 
world championship was Bruce Penhall in 1982. 
</P>
<P>
The top nine riders at Coventry will advance to the InterContinental Final on 
Aug. 12 at Fjelsted, Denmark. The World Final is scheduled for Sept. 1 at 
Bradford, England. 
</P>
</TEXT>
