<P>
CRITICS' PICKS: JACKNIFE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KEVIN THOMAS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Better scaled to TV than to the big screen, this admirable, affecting 1989 
release illuminates the lingering effects of the Vietnam War on its veterans. 
Robert De Niro (above left) stars as an uninhibited, exuberant man who 
seemingly comes out of nowhere to disrupt the ordered lives of his Vietnam 
buddy (Ed Harris, right)) and his sister (Kathy Baker). Extraordinary 
performances all around. 
</P>
<P>
Cinemax Thursday at 5 a.m. KEVIN THOMAS 
</P>
